&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is for one day per week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an Occupational Therapist looking for a part time postition to enhanceand develop your skills? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you enjoy community working in an integrated innovative Childrens Therapy team? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a good opportunity to join the NHS in a short term community post. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for Children’s Occupational Therapist, bank (or fixed term) for up to 1 year to work1 day per week . &lt;em&gt;There may be further opportunity to increase thehours for this role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;South West Hants Paediatric OT team is the largest of the Paediatric Occupational Therapy teams within Solent NHS Trust. We are an evolving proactive and strong supportive team who welcome new ideas, and who embrace flexible working. The role is in SW Hampshire, which covers Winchester &amp; Andover, Eastleigh and Southern Parishes and the New Forest, however the role will have a defined area within our locality . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a motivated ,flexible and creative Occupational Therapist who is motivated to develop their clinical skills with children . Ideally you will need to have some experience working with children and ideally some experience working in the community. The role will include managing a caseload of children . You will need to work in an autonomous way but with support. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have developed an integrated model of working with Therapy teams increasingly working together to provide holistic models of care. In addition, excellent working relationships with early years, schools, health and social care colleagues is allowing us to share our expertise more widely and create innovative ways of working together to better meet the needs of both the child and their family.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a telephone advice line and a Schools Therapy Resource Pack and we run regular INSET training to empower families, pre-schools and schools to support children at a universal and targeted level with their participation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We value our staff highly and offer full induction, clinical supervision and professional, clinical, managerial and peer support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would encourage you to contact Katya our Clinical Team Coordinator for Occupational Therapy to discuss this role in more detail via&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Katya.Gorman@solent.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 07747 022789.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
